00:50.572 --> 00:52.356
♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:52.487 --> 00:55.707
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:55.838 --> 00:58.710
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:58.841 --> 01:02.192
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.036 --> 01:21.777
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:21.907 --> 01:25.172
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:26.782 --> 01:27.957
♪ OH

01:28.566 --> 01:30.786
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:30.916 --> 01:32.527
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:32.657 --> 01:34.442
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR

01:34.572 --> 01:36.531
♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:36.661 --> 01:39.447
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:39.577 --> 01:42.885
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.015 --> 01:45.931
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:10.173 --> 02:11.174
-BREAK, BREAK.

02:11.305 --> 02:12.349
-OKAY, COME ON.

02:13.481 --> 02:14.569
-HIKE!

02:18.225 --> 02:19.400
-YOU GOT IT, DOM!

02:19.922 --> 02:21.315
-[GROWLING]

02:22.359 --> 02:24.753
-RUN!
EVERYBODY RUN!

02:26.972 --> 02:29.236
-[SCREAMING]

02:34.763 --> 02:36.373
-YEAH, THIS IS KRAMER,
TOWER TWO.

02:36.504 --> 02:38.288
ROLL BACKUP.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE
THIS ONE.

03:02.051 --> 03:03.661
-[GROWLING]

03:14.542 --> 03:16.370
-STAY ON HIM.
WE'RE RIGHT BEHIND YOU.

03:47.444 --> 03:48.532
-[GROWLING]

04:24.568 --> 04:26.004
-WAIT

04:26.135 --> 04:27.745
HEY, GUYS, WAIT A MINUTE!

04:30.966 --> 04:32.141
-[MOOING]

04:39.453 --> 04:40.671
-PLEASE, PLEASE,
DON'T HURT HIM!

04:40.802 --> 04:42.630
IT'S OKAY.
HE'S GENTLE.

04:42.760 --> 04:43.848
PLEASE!

04:43.979 --> 04:45.589
-HE'S OUR SCHOOL MASCOT.

04:45.720 --> 04:48.113
OH, SORRY.
SORRY.

04:48.244 --> 04:50.942
I MEAN, HE JUST GOT SPOOKED
WHEN SOME BALLOONS POPPED.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.729
MITCH?
MITCH BUCHANNON?

04:54.859 --> 04:56.992
TRUDY EVERSOL.
REMEMBER ME?

04:57.122 --> 04:58.602
CLASS OF '72.

04:58.733 --> 05:00.169
-TRUDY, HI.

05:00.300 --> 05:02.432
HOW YOU BEEN?
-BUSY, BUSY AS A LITTLE BEE.

05:02.563 --> 05:04.173
YOU KNOW, HOWIE AND I ARE
CHAIRING THE REUNION COMMITTEE.

05:04.304 --> 05:05.653
-[HONKING]
-GOD,

05:05.783 --> 05:07.742
I CANNOT BELIEVE YOU ARE
STILL A LIFEGUARD.

05:07.872 --> 05:08.917
-YEAH.

05:09.047 --> 05:11.093
-YOU DIDN'T RSVP.

05:11.223 --> 05:13.095
-NO.
-YOU ARE COMING THIS AFTERNOON
TO THE REUNION, AREN'T YOU?

05:13.225 --> 05:15.184
-UH, NO.
I'M SORRY, I CAN'T MAKE IT.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.360
-OH, COME ON.
YOU HAVE TO.
EVERYBODY'S GONNA BE THERE.

05:17.491 --> 05:20.015
-I'M SURE IT WILL BE
A LOT OF FUN, BUT I JUST
CAN'T MAKE IT.

05:20.145 --> 05:21.625
I'M SORRY, BUT DO ME
A FAVOR, WILL YOU?

05:21.756 --> 05:22.844
KEEP THE BULL TIED UP.

05:24.019 --> 05:25.977
NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN,
TRIXIE.

05:26.108 --> 05:27.849
-TRUDY.
-TRUDY, YEAH.

05:27.979 --> 05:29.416
SEE YA.
-YEAH.

05:36.423 --> 05:39.295
-[BABY CRYING]

05:44.256 --> 05:47.390
[CRYING CONTINUES]

05:52.787 --> 05:54.005
-HEY.

05:54.136 --> 05:55.746
SHH.

05:55.877 --> 05:57.705
COME ON, IT'S OKAY.
DON'T CRY.

05:58.749 --> 06:00.490
DON'T CRY.

06:02.231 --> 06:04.668
-[CRYING CONTINUES]

06:04.799 --> 06:06.061
-IT'S OKAY.

06:09.673 --> 06:12.110
-WOULD YOU LOOK AT THAT HAIR?
HE'S PRACTICALLY BALD.

06:12.241 --> 06:13.764
-HEY, LOOK WHO'S TALKING.

06:13.895 --> 06:15.723
-HEY!
-MITCH WAS
ON THE SWIMMING TEAM.

06:15.853 --> 06:17.377
HE TOOK IT REALLY SERIOUSLY.

06:17.507 --> 06:19.161
THE ONLY THING IN HIGH SCHOOL
HE DID.

06:19.291 --> 06:20.945
-SAY, LOOK AT THESE GIRLS.

06:21.076 --> 06:24.427
-I CAN'T BELIEVE THEY CAN
WEAR HAIR THAT HIGH.

06:24.993 --> 06:26.386
-HEY THERE, LONG TOES.

06:26.516 --> 06:28.649
I HEAR YOU TOOK THE BULL
BY THE HORNS TODAY.

06:28.779 --> 06:30.477
-UNBELIEVABLE.

06:30.607 --> 06:33.044
-LONG TOES?
-THAT WAS HIS NICKNAME
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

06:33.175 --> 06:35.264
I USED TO BRING HIM
IN MY OFFICE ALL THE TIME

06:35.395 --> 06:37.440
BECAUSE HE COULDN'T
KEEP HIS SHOES ON.

06:37.571 --> 06:39.790
-[LAUGHING]
-HE WAS MY GUIDANCE COUNSELOR.

06:40.791 --> 06:42.053
LET ME SEE THAT THING.

06:43.838 --> 06:45.448
WOW, I WONDER WHAT EVER
HAPPENED TO THAT NERD.

06:45.579 --> 06:47.755
-HEY, THEN WHY DON'T YOU
GO TO THE REUNION?
-YEAH.

06:49.626 --> 06:51.454
-ANCIENT HISTORY.

06:51.585 --> 06:53.674
-MITCH, THE ONLY REASON
THAT PEOPLE DON'T GO
TO THE REUNIONS

06:53.804 --> 06:55.632
IS IF THEY THINK THEY'RE NOT
SUCCESSFUL ENOUGH OR THEY
DON'T LOOK GOOD.

06:58.635 --> 06:59.810
-AND YOU LOOK GREAT.

06:59.941 --> 07:01.508
-IT'S THE BEST
YOU'VE EVER LOOKED.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.553
-YOU LOOK TERRIFIC.
-AND YOU ARE SUCCESSFUL, MITCH.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.816
YOU'RE MORE SUCCESSFUL
THAN MOST OF THEM.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.558
I GUARANTEE IT.
YOU KNEW WHAT YOU WANTED
TO BECOME IN HIGH SCHOOL,

07:08.689 --> 07:10.212
NOT TOO MANY PEOPLE
CAN SAY THAT.

07:10.342 --> 07:12.388
-BEN, IT'S GOT NOTHING TO DO
WITH BEING A LIFEGUARD.

07:12.519 --> 07:14.564
I'M PROUD OF THAT.
I'M VERY PROUD OF THAT.

07:14.695 --> 07:16.044
-WELL, THEN WHY AREN'T
YOU GOING?

07:16.174 --> 07:17.437
-RIGHT THERE.

07:18.438 --> 07:19.961
-BECAUSE GAYLE'S GOING.

07:20.091 --> 07:22.746
-LAST TIME I SAW EVERYBODY,
WE WERE STILL MARRIED.

07:23.747 --> 07:25.749
NOW, WE'RE DIVORCED.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.359
EVERYBODY'S GOING TO COME UP
TO ME AND SAY,
"OH, WHAT A SHAME.

07:27.882 --> 07:29.884
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHO GOT HOBIE?"

07:30.014 --> 07:31.929
I CAN'T DEAL WITH THAT.
NO WAY.

07:32.060 --> 07:34.584
-HERE WE GO.
-[BABY CRYING]

07:35.846 --> 07:38.936
-GUYS, WOULD ONE
OF YOU PLEASE...

07:39.067 --> 07:40.460
PLEASE TAKE THIS THING,
HUH?

07:40.590 --> 07:42.418
-IT'S NOT A THING.
IT'S A BABY.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.899
-YEAH, YEAH.

07:45.421 --> 07:47.379
-MITCH: WHOSE BABY?
-I HAVE NO IDEA.

07:47.510 --> 07:49.991
I FOUND IT-- HER,
UNDERNEATH MY TOWER

07:50.121 --> 07:52.515
ALONG WITH THIS NOTE.
WAIT TILL YOU GUYS
HEAR THIS.

07:52.646 --> 07:55.518
-I'VE STOPPED BABY TEARS
ALL MY LIFE. COULD I HOLD HER,
PLEASE?

07:55.649 --> 07:56.519
-SURE.

07:56.650 --> 07:58.826
-"DEAR LIFEGUARD,

07:58.956 --> 08:00.958
"I KNOW YOUR JOB IS TO SAVE
PEOPLE WHO ARE IN TROUBLE
ON THE BEACH,

08:01.089 --> 08:03.874
"SO PLEASE KEEP MY BABY SAFE
FOR 24 HOURS.

08:04.832 --> 08:07.835
"I'LL BE BACK TO GET HER,
AND PLEASE DON'T CALL
THE AUTHORITIES.

08:08.488 --> 08:09.967
"I LOVE MY BABY VERY MUCH

08:10.098 --> 08:13.144
AND I'D DIE IF SHE WAS
EVER TAKEN AWAY FROM ME."

08:13.275 --> 08:17.018
-HOPEFULLY THERE ARE OTHER
FINGERPRINTS ON THIS
THAN YOUR OWN.

08:17.148 --> 08:19.020
HEINZ, GIVE THIS TO JONNY,
WILL YOU?
-I GOT IT.

08:19.150 --> 08:21.065
-DID YOU SEE ANYBODY
AT THE BEACH TODAY

08:21.196 --> 08:22.719
WHO MIGHT HAVE
POSSIBLY LEFT HER?

08:22.850 --> 08:25.461
-NO, MUST HAVE
SNUCK UP FROM BEHIND.

08:25.592 --> 08:27.202
-HERE, BEN, LET ME TRY.

08:27.332 --> 08:29.160
I HAD A PATENTED WAY
OF KEEPING HOBIE FROM CRYING.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.380
COME HERE,
LITTLE BABY.

08:31.511 --> 08:34.470
-[CRYING CONTINUES]
-YEAH.

08:34.601 --> 08:36.037
MAYBE YOU'RE JUST
WORSE WITH BOYS.

08:37.734 --> 08:39.519
-[STAMMERS]

08:39.649 --> 08:41.607
OH.
-[CRYING CONTINUES]

08:43.260 --> 08:45.133
[CRYING STOPS]

08:50.530 --> 08:52.749
-WHAT? WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
LOOKING AT ME LIKE THAT FOR?

08:52.880 --> 08:54.925
-YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
THE BABY DOESN'T
CRY WITH.

08:55.056 --> 08:58.015
WELL, IT ISN'T BECAUSE OF ME.
I DON'T KNOW A THING
ABOUT BABIES.

08:58.146 --> 08:59.887
COME ON.
-THE QUESTION IS...

09:00.801 --> 09:02.585
DO WE CONTACT
THE AUTHORITIES

09:02.716 --> 09:04.239
OR DO WHAT
THE NOTE SAYS?

09:04.369 --> 09:06.284
-BEN, WHOEVER ABANDONED HER
TOOK A BIG CHANCE

09:06.415 --> 09:07.677
HE MIGHT NOT FIND HER.

09:07.808 --> 09:09.853
-YEAH, BUT HE DID,

09:09.984 --> 09:11.638
AND WHOEVER WROTE THAT NOTE
IS OBVIOUSLY IN A LOT
OF TROUBLE.

09:11.768 --> 09:13.988
SO I THINK MAYBE WE SHOULD
WAIT THE 24 HOURS

09:14.118 --> 09:15.946
AND THEN IF THEY DON'T SHOW UP
WE CAN CALL CHILD WELFARE.

09:16.077 --> 09:18.296
-YOU'RE THE GUIDANCE COUNSELOR,
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

09:18.427 --> 09:20.168
-DOES IT HURT TO WAIT
THE 24 HOURS?

09:20.298 --> 09:21.648
-WHAT DO WE DO
WITH HER IN THE MEANTIME?

09:21.778 --> 09:23.171
I MEAN, WHO'S GONNA
TAKE CARE OF HER?

09:24.520 --> 09:25.565
-[CLEARS THROAT]

09:27.044 --> 09:29.090
-NO WAY.
UH-UH.

09:32.397 --> 09:35.052
-YOU KNOW, I THINK IT COULD BE
TIME TO CHANGE HER DIAPER,
EDDIE.

09:35.183 --> 09:36.576
-YEAH, I GOTTA GO.

09:36.706 --> 09:38.752
-JOHNNY.
-A TAXI FOR ME?
I GOTTA GO.

09:38.882 --> 09:40.536
-I GOTTA MAKE A PHONE CALL.

09:40.667 --> 09:42.538
-BUDDY. BEN.

09:42.669 --> 09:44.627
HEY, COME ON, MAN.
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LEAVE ME,
ARE YOU?

09:44.758 --> 09:45.672
-WATCH ME.

09:46.237 --> 09:47.674
-BUT YOU--

09:52.417 --> 09:53.505
-HOBIE, I'M HOME.

09:56.465 --> 09:58.249
WHOA!

09:58.380 --> 10:00.295
WOW, THAT'S A BIG HUG.

10:00.425 --> 10:02.210
I WAS ONLY AWAY
FOR A FEW HOURS.

10:07.476 --> 10:08.695
GAYLE.

10:08.825 --> 10:10.261
-HOW ARE YOU, MITCH?

10:11.001 --> 10:12.002
-OH.

10:20.228 --> 10:23.231
-THAT IS A SILLY REASON
NOT TO GO TO THIS REUNION.

10:23.361 --> 10:26.364
-I KNOW, DAD.
YOU ALWAYS TELL ME IT DOESN'T
MATTER WHAT OTHER PEOPLE THINK.

10:26.495 --> 10:27.801
-THIS TIME IT'S DIFFERENT.

10:27.931 --> 10:29.280
-OH, COME ON.

10:29.411 --> 10:31.152
CHUCK BIZANNI'S COMING
ALL THE WAY FROM ASPEN.

10:31.282 --> 10:32.719
STEVE ROY'S GONNA BE THERE.

10:32.849 --> 10:34.851
YOU GUYS HAVEN'T SEEN
EACH OTHER IN YEARS.

10:34.982 --> 10:37.201
-DON'T YOU THINK IT WILL
LOOK FUNNY, YOU AND I
WALKING IN TOGETHER?

10:37.332 --> 10:40.465
NO, IN FACT, I THINK IT WOULD
BE GREAT FOR PEOPLE TO SEE

10:40.596 --> 10:43.120
THAT JUST 'CAUSE WE GOT
A DIVORCE DOESN'T MEAN THAT WE
CAN'T STILL BE FRIENDS.

10:43.251 --> 10:45.035
-AND MAYBE EVEN
GET BACK TOGETHER.

10:45.688 --> 10:47.298
-DON'T COUNT ON THAT, PAL.

10:47.429 --> 10:49.649
-YOU DON'T KNOW FOR SURE.
I MEAN, IT COULD HAPPEN.

10:50.562 --> 10:52.390
-ANYWAY, I CAN'T GO
BECAUSE...

10:53.174 --> 10:55.393
I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO WEAR.

10:55.524 --> 10:57.482
WELL, IT JUST SO HAPPENS
THAT I BROUGHT YOU SOMETHING

10:57.613 --> 10:59.093
SO NOW YOU DON'T HAVE
ANY EXCUSES.

10:59.223 --> 11:01.225
SO COME ON.
-WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
HOLD IT.

11:01.356 --> 11:02.792
WHO'S GONNA TAKE CARE
OF HOBIE?

11:02.923 --> 11:04.620
-I'M STAYING
AT JEREMY'S HOUSE.

11:04.751 --> 11:06.709
-AND I'M GONNA PICK
HIM UP IN THE MORNING

11:06.840 --> 11:08.189
AND WE'RE GONNA SPEND
THE WHOLE DAY TOGETHER
BEFORE I HAVE TO LEAVE.

11:08.319 --> 11:09.843
RIGHT? SO.
-RIGHT.

11:09.973 --> 11:14.021
-UH, GAYLE, I DON'T THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

11:14.151 --> 11:15.544
-DON'T WORRY.

11:16.066 --> 11:18.155
LOOK, I GOT IN LATE SO I CAME
STRAIGHT HERE FROM THE AIRPORT,

11:18.286 --> 11:20.549
BUT I'M GONNA CHECK INTO
A HOTEL RIGHT AFTER THE REUNION.

11:23.639 --> 11:24.814
-OKAY.

11:25.467 --> 11:26.773
I STILL DON'T WANT TO GO.

11:31.299 --> 11:34.302
[SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

11:34.432 --> 11:36.696
-WHOA, DAD.
THIS IS AWESOME.

11:36.826 --> 11:39.437
-YEAH, I CAN'T BELIEVE YOUR MOM
KEPT IT ALL THESE YEARS.

11:39.568 --> 11:41.701
I GAVE THIS TO HER WHEN WE
FIRST STARTED GOING STEADY.

11:41.831 --> 11:43.093
-HOW OLD WERE
YOU GUYS?

11:43.615 --> 11:44.704
-17.

11:45.574 --> 11:46.662
-TA-DA.

11:46.793 --> 11:48.620
-WOW.
-WOW.

11:49.230 --> 11:51.275
-HEY, YOU LOOK PRETTY GOOD.
THAT JACKET STILL FITS YOU
I SEE.

11:51.406 --> 11:53.277
-YEP.
-SO, YOU GUYS
READY TO GO?

11:53.408 --> 11:54.844
-YEAH.
-YEAH. ONE THING.

11:54.975 --> 11:56.063
I THINK WE SHOULD
TAKE TWO CARS.

11:56.193 --> 11:57.804
-LOOK, I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.

11:57.934 --> 11:59.936
IF IT REALLY MAKES YOU
THIS UPTIGHT

12:00.067 --> 12:01.721
FOR ME TO BE THERE,
THEN WHY DON'T I JUST
STAY HERE WITH HOBIE

12:01.851 --> 12:03.113
AND YOU CAN GO ALONE.

12:03.244 --> 12:04.898
-GAYLE, I DIDN'T MEAN THAT.
-MOM?

12:05.028 --> 12:06.900
YOU CAME ALL THE WAY
FROM OHIO TO GO
TO THIS REUNION.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.945
-YEAH, WELL, I ALSO
CAME TO SEE YOU.

12:09.076 --> 12:11.643
-TELL YOU WHAT, I NEVER WANTED
TO GO IN THE FIRST PLACE,

12:11.774 --> 12:13.167
YOU GO, I'LL STAY
HERE WITH HOBIE.

12:13.297 --> 12:14.995
-MITCH, WE DON'T HAVE
TO WALK IN TOGETHER.

12:15.125 --> 12:16.431
WE DON'T EVEN HAVE
TO BE WITH EACH OTHER.

12:16.561 --> 12:18.302
LET'S JUST GO, WE'LL HAVE
A GOOD TIME,

12:18.433 --> 12:20.522
THEN YOU DRIVE ME BACK HERE,
I GET MY STUFF AND I CHECK OUT.

12:21.958 --> 12:23.090
-ALL RIGHT.

12:24.004 --> 12:26.267
THANKS FOR THE JACKET.

12:26.397 --> 12:28.269
-SINCE WE WEREN'T GOING
STEADY ANYMORE, I REALLY
THOUGHT YOU SHOULD HAVE IT.

12:28.922 --> 12:30.184
-COME ON.
-COME ON.

12:32.055 --> 12:35.189
-♪ JEREMIAH WAS A BULLFROG

12:35.798 --> 12:38.279
♪ WAS A GOOD FRIEND
OF MINE ♪

12:39.541 --> 12:42.762
♪ I NEVER UNDERSTOOD
A SINGLE WORD HE SAID ♪

12:42.892 --> 12:45.373
♪ BUT I HELPED HIM
DRINK HIS WINE ♪

12:46.591 --> 12:49.246
♪ AND HE ALWAYS HAD
SOME MIGHTY FINE WINE ♪

12:49.377 --> 12:51.074
-TELL ME, WHAT WAS
THE MOST EMBARRASSING THING

12:51.205 --> 12:52.728
THAT EVER HAPPENED
TO YOU IN HIGH SCHOOL?

12:52.859 --> 12:54.556
-[LAUGHING]

12:58.212 --> 13:00.127
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

13:00.257 --> 13:02.694
-LOOKING GOOD, MAN.
-SO ARE YOU.
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

13:02.825 --> 13:04.609
-I HAVEN'T LOOKED THIS GOOD
IN A LONG TIME, MAN.

13:05.785 --> 13:09.179
-♪ IF I WERE
THE KING OF THE WORLD ♪

13:09.310 --> 13:11.921
♪ TELL YOU
WHAT I'D DO ♪

13:13.009 --> 13:16.796
♪ I'D THROW AWAY THE CARS
AND THE BARS AND THE WARS ♪

13:16.926 --> 13:19.407
♪ AND MAKE
SWEET LOVE TO YOU ♪

13:22.105 --> 13:23.411
-BEER.

13:24.673 --> 13:28.242
-♪ ALL THE BOYS AND GIRLS

13:28.372 --> 13:31.854
♪ JOY TO THE FISHES
IN THE DEEP BLUE SEA ♪

13:31.985 --> 13:34.683
♪ JOY TO YOU AND ME

13:39.383 --> 13:42.125
-[SCREAMS]
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

13:43.344 --> 13:44.867
[CHATTERING]

13:46.651 --> 13:48.610
-WE WOULD TALK
ALL THE TIME, DIDN'T WE?

13:48.740 --> 13:50.481
[SHRIEKING]

13:51.004 --> 13:53.833
-♪ YOU KNOW I LOVE
THE LADIES ♪

13:54.877 --> 13:57.314
♪ LOVE TO HAVE MY FUN

13:57.924 --> 14:01.841
♪ I'M A HIGH NIGHT FLIER
AND A RAINBOW RIDER ♪

14:01.971 --> 14:04.626
♪ A STRAIGHT-SHOOTIN'
SON OF A GUN ♪

14:04.756 --> 14:07.368
-[LAUGHING]
-HEY.

14:08.978 --> 14:13.200
-♪ I'M SINGING
JOY TO THE WORLD ♪

14:13.330 --> 14:16.246
-[IDLE CHATTERING]

14:17.682 --> 14:20.337
-I NEED TO GO TALK TO MY WIFE.
EX-WIFE.

14:20.990 --> 14:24.211
-♪ JOY TO YOU AND ME

14:24.341 --> 14:26.778
-TELL ME, WHAT WAS THE MOST
EMBARRASSING THING THAT EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU IN HIGH SCHOOL?

14:26.909 --> 14:27.997
-PLEASE.

14:28.955 --> 14:30.173
GOD.

14:35.831 --> 14:37.833
-MITCH BUCHANNON.
-WHAT?

14:37.964 --> 14:39.966
-I WAS HOPING
I'D SEE YOU.

14:40.096 --> 14:42.533
YOU HAVEN'T CHANGED
AT ALL.

14:43.795 --> 14:47.364
-WELL, OBVIOUSLY YOU HAVE,
BECAUSE I HAVE NO IDEA
WHO YOU ARE.

14:47.495 --> 14:50.063
AND IF YOU LOOKED LIKE THIS
IN HIGH SCHOOL, I THINK
I WOULD REMEMBER.

14:50.193 --> 14:51.847
-I SAT BEHIND YOU FOR YEARS.

14:54.284 --> 14:55.372
-TRISH BUCKLEY?

14:56.678 --> 14:58.723
-YEP.

14:58.854 --> 15:01.030
FATED BY ALPHABETICAL ORDER
TO KNOW EVERY CURL
OF YOUR HAIR.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.772
UNTIL YOU SHAVED IT OFF.
-MM.

15:03.903 --> 15:05.992
-DID YOU KNOW
I ACTUALLY CRIED THAT DAY?

15:06.122 --> 15:07.471
-NO, I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

15:07.602 --> 15:08.951
-I DID.

15:09.821 --> 15:11.345
YOU HAD SUCH BEAUTIFUL HAIR.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.132
