YOU'RE WEARING SHOES.

15:16.828 --> 15:19.744
-AND I'M SURPRISED YOU'RE
NOT WEARING A SIZE 12 DRESS,

15:19.875 --> 15:21.529
HORN-RIMMED GLASSES,
AND BRACES.

15:21.659 --> 15:23.444
-WELL, SOME PEOPLE
PEAK IN HIGH SCHOOL.

15:24.358 --> 15:25.968
-STILL A WHIZ AT SCIENCE?

15:26.099 --> 15:28.057
-I OWN A COMPUTER SOFTWARE
COMPANY.

15:28.188 --> 15:30.451
-[LAUGHS]

15:30.581 --> 15:32.453
WELL, YOU DEFINITELY HAVE
ALL THE RIGHT REASONS TO COME
TO THIS REUNION.

15:34.324 --> 15:35.499
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

15:36.022 --> 15:37.719
-[SIGHS]

15:41.288 --> 15:46.162
-♪ NOW THAT I CAN DANCE

15:46.293 --> 15:49.296
-[HARMONIZING]

15:51.341 --> 15:53.561
-WATCH ME NOW!
-HEY!

15:53.691 --> 15:54.779
-HOW ARE YOU GUYS?

15:54.910 --> 15:56.129
-WHOA, HOW ARE YOU?

15:56.259 --> 15:57.695
-HOW ARE YOU DOING, MAN?
-I'M DOING OKAY.

15:57.826 --> 15:59.480
MY HANDS HURT
FROM THAT CLAP THOUGH.

16:01.525 --> 16:03.919
-[LULLABY PLAYING]

16:04.050 --> 16:05.747
-[BABY CRYING]

16:06.487 --> 16:08.054
-DON'T CRY.
IT'S OKAY.

16:08.184 --> 16:10.099
-EDDIE, DON'T HOLD
THE BABY LIKE THAT.

16:10.230 --> 16:12.014
YOU HAVE TO CRADLE HER
IN YOUR ARMS.

16:12.145 --> 16:14.886
OH, IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.
YOU MEAN LIKE A FOOTBALL?

16:15.017 --> 16:17.802
-YES.
-YEAH, HOW'S THAT?
IS THAT BETTER, HUH?

16:17.933 --> 16:19.543
GO OUT FOR A PASS.

16:19.674 --> 16:21.937
I'M KIDDING.
I WAS JUST KIDDING, COME ON.

16:23.330 --> 16:26.637
-NOW COMES THE FUN PART.

16:27.725 --> 16:29.640
-OH, NO, NO.
I DON'T WANT ANYTHING
TO DO WITH THAT.

16:29.771 --> 16:31.468
-COME ON.
BE BRAVE.

16:31.599 --> 16:33.296
JUST SET HER DOWN RIGHT HERE.
-I'M GONNA PUT YOU DOWN.

16:33.427 --> 16:35.342
OH YEAH.

16:35.472 --> 16:38.258
WHOOP, THERE YOU GO.
WATCH OUT FOR YOUR
LITTLE HEAD THERE.

16:38.388 --> 16:39.650
THERE YOU GO.

16:40.651 --> 16:42.914
-GO AHEAD.
TAKE THE OLD ONE OFF.

16:43.045 --> 16:44.742
-OH, NO, NO.
I'M NOT GOING IN THERE.

16:44.873 --> 16:46.396
-YOU KNOW, SOMEBODY
HAD TO DO THIS FOR YOU.

16:46.527 --> 16:48.355
-THAT'S PROBABLY WHY
I WAS PUT UP FOR ADOPTION.

16:51.575 --> 16:53.360
I'M GONNA GET YOU FOR THIS.

16:54.578 --> 16:55.492
OKAY.

16:56.319 --> 16:57.538
ALL RIGHT.

16:59.844 --> 17:01.324
-HEY.
-GOOD GIRL.

17:01.455 --> 17:02.238
-YEAH.

17:02.369 --> 17:04.719
OH, CALL 911.

17:06.155 --> 17:08.549
OKAY. WHEW.

17:08.679 --> 17:10.942
-OH, IT'S NOT THAT BAD.
-YES, IT STINKS.

17:11.073 --> 17:13.162
VERY BAD.
-WIPE.

17:15.425 --> 17:17.384
-[WHISPERS]
YOU STINK.

17:19.473 --> 17:21.474
-YEAH.
POWDER.

17:21.605 --> 17:22.737
EASY.

17:29.831 --> 17:31.702
-[CLEARS THROAT]
-DIAPER.

17:32.877 --> 17:34.705
-UH, WHAT DO I DO WITH THAT?

17:34.836 --> 17:36.403
-SEE THIS TAPE?
-UH-HUH.

17:36.533 --> 17:37.752
-PULL 'EM OUT AND JUST WRAP IT
AROUND THE FRONT.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.450
YOU GOT IT.
-OKAY. OKAY.

17:41.495 --> 17:43.018
IT WAS A PIECE OF CAKE,
HUH?

17:43.149 --> 17:44.759
-PIECE OF CAKE.
-YES, IT'S A PIECE OF CAKE.

17:45.890 --> 17:47.370
-YES.
HUH, HOW'S THAT?

17:48.197 --> 17:49.938
-NOT BAD, MR. MOM.
-MM-HMM.

17:50.069 --> 17:52.288
-WHAT'D I TELL YOU?
THIS IS A PIECE OF CAKE,
HUH?

17:53.376 --> 17:55.248
SHE SMILED.
SHE SMILED AT ME.

17:55.378 --> 17:57.032
SHE ACTUALLY SMILED AT ME.
-SHE DID SMILE AT YOU.

17:57.163 --> 17:58.599
-COME HERE, YOU.
COME HERE.

17:58.729 --> 18:00.296
WORK WITH ME, WILL YOU?
THANKS.

18:02.342 --> 18:04.866
-[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

18:08.174 --> 18:12.091
-NO, NO. GAYLE, YOU HAVE TO
SAY IT LOUD ENOUGH SO THE
WHOLE WORLD CAN HEAR IT.

18:12.221 --> 18:15.442
NOW, WHAT WAS THE MOST
EMBARRASSING MOMENT YOU
EVER HAD IN HIGH SCHOOL?

18:16.791 --> 18:18.967
-OKAY, OKAY.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.012
THE MOST EMBARRASSING THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO ME
IN HIGH SCHOOL--

18:21.143 --> 18:23.493
-THE TIME THAT YOU GOT
CAUGHT WITH ME
IN THE BOY'S LOCKER ROOM.

18:23.624 --> 18:25.626
-HEY, I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.
-SURE YOU DO.

18:25.756 --> 18:27.758
I'M THE ONE YOU ALWAYS WANTED.

18:27.889 --> 18:29.804
YOU KNOW, THE GUY
THAT YOU WERE TOO SHY
TO COME AFTER BACK THEN.

18:29.934 --> 18:32.067
-[STAMMERING]

18:32.198 --> 18:33.590
-I ALWAYS WANTED TO KISS YOU.

18:33.721 --> 18:35.375
ONE FOR THE CAMERA.
JUST ONE FOR THE CAMERA.

18:36.463 --> 18:37.812
-THAT'S ENOUGH!

18:41.859 --> 18:43.992
YOU'VE COME A LONG WAY
SINCE HIGH SCHOOL,
HAVEN'T YOU?

18:44.601 --> 18:46.037
-MITCH, LET HIM GO.

18:46.647 --> 18:48.257
-AS SOON AS HE APOLOGIZES.

18:48.388 --> 18:49.998
-WHAT DO YOU GIVE A DAMN FOR?
I HEARD SHE DUMPED YOU.

18:50.129 --> 18:52.348
-THE ONLY ONE BEING
DUMPED ON AT THE MOMENT
IS YOU.

18:52.479 --> 18:53.958
NOW, SAY YOU'RE SORRY.

18:54.089 --> 18:55.743
-FOR EVERYTHING YOU'VE
EVER DONE TO ANYONE HERE.

18:55.873 --> 18:57.832
-YEAH!
-I'M GONNA GET BOTH OF YOU--

18:58.572 --> 19:00.226
-SAY YOU'RE SORRY.

19:01.488 --> 19:03.098
-SORRY.

19:03.229 --> 19:05.187
-NOW, SAY IT LOUD ENOUGH
FOR EVERYBODY IN HERE TO HEAR.

19:05.840 --> 19:07.624
GO ON.
-I'M SORRY, OKAY!

19:08.147 --> 19:10.279
-[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

19:11.411 --> 19:14.675
-YOU KNOW, YOU ALWAYS THOUGHT
YOU WERE A HOTSHOT, BUCHANNON.

19:14.805 --> 19:16.503
WELL, YOU AIN'T NOTHING.

19:16.633 --> 19:18.113
I OWN THREE
AUTO PARTS STORES,

19:18.244 --> 19:19.462
AND I MAKE
MORE MONEY IN A MONTH

19:19.593 --> 19:21.421
THAN YOU MAKE IN A YEAR
ON THE BEACH.

19:23.031 --> 19:24.902
NO WONDER SHE DUMPED YOU.

19:30.604 --> 19:32.258
-SORRY ABOUT THAT.
ARE YOU OKAY?

19:32.954 --> 19:34.173
-YOU'RE MY HERO.

19:36.566 --> 19:38.264
-LET'S GET SOME AIR, HUH?

19:41.267 --> 19:42.398
-BEER.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.931
-[WHISTLES]
IT'S TIME TO EAT.

19:54.062 --> 19:57.370
IT'S NOT CAFETERIA FOOD,
TRUST ME.

20:15.214 --> 20:17.999
-[FUNK MUSIC PLAYING]

20:35.799 --> 20:37.497
-MITCH, YOU HAVE TO.
-NO WAY.

20:37.627 --> 20:39.325
-COME ON, MAN.
WE ALREADY TALKED TO THE BAND.

20:39.455 --> 20:41.718
-IT'S BEEN 20 YEARS, PAL.
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

20:41.849 --> 20:44.025
IT'S PERFECT, LIKE WE
REHEARSED IT YESTERDAY.

20:44.155 --> 20:44.982
-NO.
-COME ON, WE'LL
BLOW 'EM AWAY.

20:45.113 --> 20:46.593
-OH, COME ON, MITCH.

20:46.723 --> 20:48.856
-NOT YOU. NOT YOU.
DON'T YOU-- NO.

20:48.986 --> 20:50.901
-MITCH, PLEASE, IT'LL BE FUN.
-DON'T EMBARRASS ME.

20:54.122 --> 20:55.863
-♪ YOU BROKE MY HEART

20:57.299 --> 20:59.258
