23:39.113 --> 23:40.593
MAYBE WE SHOULD
OPEN THE DOORS.

23:40.723 --> 23:42.290
NO, NO, WE CAN'T DO THAT,
'CAUSE THEN SHE'D

23:42.421 --> 23:44.640
CATCH A COLD BECAUSE
IT'D BE TOO COLD FOR HER.

23:44.771 --> 23:45.946
[BABY VOICE]
OH YES.

23:47.774 --> 23:49.123
I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG
WITH THIS BOTTLE

23:49.253 --> 23:50.994
MAYBE THE TEMPERATURE'S
NOT RIGHT OR SOMETHING.

23:51.125 --> 23:53.519
MAYBE THE NIPPLE'S
A LITTLE CLOGGED.
-EDDIE, SWEETIE.

23:53.649 --> 23:55.999
IT'S OKAY.
LET ME HAVE THE BABY.

23:56.130 --> 23:57.348
SHE'S ALMOST ASLEEP.

23:57.479 --> 23:59.089
-OH, BABY.
-EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

23:59.655 --> 24:01.440
-OH, YES.
-HI, SWEETIE.

24:01.570 --> 24:04.486
WE'RE GONNA MAKE YOU COMFY.
-OH YEAH.

24:05.313 --> 24:07.141
-THAT'S COMFY.
THAT'S GOOD.

24:07.271 --> 24:08.403
-YEAH.

24:12.494 --> 24:15.018
-I WANNA HAVE THREE BABIES.

24:15.671 --> 24:17.325
I WANT TO HAVE TWO BOYS
AND A GIRL.

24:18.369 --> 24:21.895
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
YOU KNOW THAT WE HAVE NEVER
EVEN TALKED ABOUT THAT BEFORE?

24:22.025 --> 24:23.418
-I DON'T KNOW.

24:24.071 --> 24:26.116
ALL I KNOW IS WHEN
I BECOME A FATHER,

24:26.247 --> 24:28.467
THE MOTHER AND I
ARE GONNA STAY
TOGETHER FOREVER.

24:29.772 --> 24:31.818
NO FIGHTS, NO BREAKUPS.

24:35.082 --> 24:38.302
I WENT THROUGH ALL THAT HELL
AND I SWORE MY KID WOULD
NEVER GO THROUGH IT.

24:43.612 --> 24:46.833
-YEAH, BUT THERE'S NO SUCH THING
AS A 100% GUARANTEE, EDDIE.

24:47.964 --> 24:49.313
I MEAN, ALL YOU CAN DO IS...

24:50.271 --> 24:51.751
DO THE BEST YOU CAN.

24:51.881 --> 24:53.883
ONE DAY AT A TIME
WITH THE PERSON YOU LOVE.

24:55.102 --> 24:56.625
-YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

24:58.758 --> 25:00.237
YOU KNOW ANYONE
I CAN DO THAT WITH?

25:00.368 --> 25:01.935
-OH, VERY FUNNY.
HA HA.

25:02.065 --> 25:04.024
-SHH, YOU'RE GONNA
WAKE THE BABY.

25:04.154 --> 25:06.983
-OH, SHUT UP
AND KISS ME WILL YOU?
BABY, BABY, BABY.

25:07.114 --> 25:08.637
-OH, I LOVE YOU TOO.

25:08.768 --> 25:11.074
-SHAUNI DOESN'T GET
ANY ATTENTION.

25:11.205 --> 25:12.598
-SHUT UP AND KISS ME.

25:15.122 --> 25:17.820
-SEEING THE THREE OF YOU
UP THERE, IT FELT LIKE WE WERE
BACK IN HIGH SCHOOL.

25:17.951 --> 25:19.169
REALLY.

25:19.822 --> 25:22.259
-THANKS.
-FOR WHAT?

25:22.390 --> 25:24.479
-FOR MAKING ME COME.
I'M HAVING A GREAT TIME.

25:24.610 --> 25:26.525
-[LAUGHING]

25:26.655 --> 25:28.178
-TELL ME SOMETHING.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.268
DO I LOOK, YOU KNOW,

25:31.399 --> 25:33.749
VERY DIFFERENT THAN I DID
BACK IN HIGH SCHOOL?

25:33.880 --> 25:36.404
-WHY ARE YOU SO INSECURE?
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

25:36.535 --> 25:38.493
YOU LOOK AS BEAUTIFUL
AS EVER.

25:38.624 --> 25:41.278
-OH GOOD. THAT MEANS ALL
THE FACIALS AND WORKOUTS
HAVE BEEN WORTH IT.

25:41.409 --> 25:42.932
-[LAUGHS]

25:43.063 --> 25:45.021
-WE CAME OUT HERE THE DAY
OF OUR PROM, REMEMBER?

25:45.544 --> 25:47.284
RIGHT AFTER
THE DANCING STARTED.

25:48.416 --> 25:50.636
-YEP, WE SNUCK OUT HERE
TO BE ALONE.

25:51.941 --> 25:52.768
-DO YOU WANT TO?

25:53.682 --> 25:54.553
-WHAT?

25:55.684 --> 25:57.077
-TAKE OFF
AND BE ALONE.

25:59.383 --> 26:00.471
-WE'RE OUTTA HERE.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.483
-WE SHOULD GET A CAMERA.

26:12.614 --> 26:14.790
TAKE A PICTURE OF HIS FACE
WHEN THE WAVE HITS HIM.

26:16.226 --> 26:18.141
HE WAKES UP
AND SEES WHERE HE IS.

26:18.272 --> 26:20.013
-[BOTH LAUGHING]

26:20.143 --> 26:23.103
-I'M NOT GONNA NEED A PICTURE
TO REMEMBER THIS MOMENT.

26:23.233 --> 26:25.409
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR 20 YEARS
TO GET BACK AT HIM.

26:25.540 --> 26:27.629
[LAUGHING]

26:29.979 --> 26:32.286
-I THINK ABOUT YOU
A LOT, MITCH.

26:32.416 --> 26:34.331
I MEAN, I MISS YOU.

26:36.551 --> 26:37.944
-I MISS YOU TOO.

26:41.643 --> 26:44.472
-I GOTTA TELL YOU, YOU'RE DOING
A GREAT JOB WITH HOBIE.

26:45.081 --> 26:47.388
REALLY, IT MAKES IT
SO MUCH EASIER

26:47.518 --> 26:48.955
FOR ME TO DEAL WITH
BEING AWAY FROM HIM

26:49.085 --> 26:50.609
JUST KNOWING
THAT HE'S WITH YOU.

26:51.958 --> 26:52.828
-THANKS.

26:54.221 --> 26:55.352
THAT MEANS A LOT.

26:56.310 --> 26:58.399
-[LAUGHING]

27:02.925 --> 27:04.405
-WHAT THE?
-HEY, VERON.

27:04.535 --> 27:06.189
-HEY, LAR.
-HOW YOU DOING, BUDDY?

27:08.104 --> 27:09.932
-DIG ME OUT OF HERE.
I'M GONNA KILL YOU BOTH.

27:10.063 --> 27:13.153
-[OOHING, LAUGHING]

27:13.283 --> 27:15.851
-MAYBE IF YOU BEG US,
WE WILL, VERON.

27:15.982 --> 27:17.723
-YEAH.
-COME ON, VERON, BEG.

27:21.248 --> 27:23.163
BEG A LITTLE BIT.
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

27:23.293 --> 27:24.512
COME ON, BEG.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.732
-[BOTH LAUGHING]

27:29.343 --> 27:30.997
-UH, SHOULD WE--

27:31.606 --> 27:32.999
MAYBE WE SHOULD
DIG HIM OUT.

27:33.129 --> 27:34.609
-COME ON, HE'S THE ONE
SUPPOSED TO PANIC.

27:34.740 --> 27:35.915
NOT US.

27:38.178 --> 27:39.875
-THIS IS WHERE HOBIE
GOT STARTED.

27:41.660 --> 27:43.531
-NO, I THINK IT WAS
DOWN THE BEACH--

27:43.662 --> 27:45.838
-ALL RIGHT, IT'S WHERE WE
GOT STARTED DOING WHAT
STARTED HIM.

27:49.624 --> 27:52.322
HOW WE WAITED UNTIL
OUR SENIOR PROM NIGHT
I'LL NEVER KNOW.

27:52.453 --> 27:55.195
-WASN'T ME.
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO KEPT SAYING NO.

27:57.110 --> 27:58.677
-WELL, I WON'T
SAY NO TONIGHT.

28:13.779 --> 28:16.129
THAT'S ONE OF THE THINGS
ABOUT YOU I MISSED THE MOST.

28:30.273 --> 28:32.101
-YEAH.
[LAUGHS]

28:32.232 --> 28:34.582
BEG, COME ON.
BEG, VERON!

28:35.235 --> 28:37.237
BEG, LIKE ON PROM NIGHT,

28:37.367 --> 28:39.326
WHEN I BEGGED YOU
TO LEAVE ME ALONE

28:39.456 --> 28:42.546
AND YOU CHASED ME
OUT INTO THE OCEAN
IN FRONT OF EVERYBODY.

28:42.677 --> 28:43.983
IN FRONT OF MY DATE!

28:44.113 --> 28:46.768
-DIG ME OUT.
PLEASE, COME ON.
PLEASE!

28:46.899 --> 28:47.943
PLEASE!

28:48.074 --> 28:50.119
-NO.
-HOWIE.

28:57.692 --> 28:58.867
-YOU SEE HOW SCARED
HE IS?

28:58.998 --> 29:00.434
-HOWIE, THE TIDE
IS GETTING HIGHER.

29:03.567 --> 29:05.787
-COME ON.

29:05.918 --> 29:07.658
WE'LL DIG HIM OUT FAR ENOUGH
THAT HE CAN GET THE REST
OF THE WAY OUT HIMSELF,

29:07.789 --> 29:10.313
THEN WE RUN. OKAY?
-ALL RIGHT. YEAH. GOOD.

29:24.980 --> 29:27.113
THE WATER'S FILLING UP
THE HOLE, HOWIE.

29:30.029 --> 29:31.508
WE BETTER GET HIM
OUT OF HERE.

29:37.210 --> 29:38.515
-MAN: HELP!

29:39.255 --> 29:40.866
HELP US!

29:40.996 --> 29:42.084
HELP!

29:46.175 --> 29:48.525
[MAN SHOUTING]

29:49.091 --> 29:50.876
HELP!

29:51.006 --> 29:52.138
-WHAT IS IT?

29:52.791 --> 29:54.009
-I DON'T KNOW.

29:57.404 --> 29:58.797
-MITCH! MITCH!

29:58.927 --> 30:00.146
QUICK, THAT'S VERON.

30:00.276 --> 30:02.148
WE BURIED HIM.
-I CAN'T GET HIM OUT!

30:02.278 --> 30:03.671
-WE WERE JUST TRYING
TO PUT A SCARE IN HIM.

30:03.802 --> 30:04.890
-GET THAT TRASH CAN
OVER THERE.
HURRY!

30:14.725 --> 30:16.292
-OH MY GOD.
WHAT CAN I DO?

30:16.423 --> 30:17.554
-GET THE SHOVEL.

30:44.799 --> 30:45.931
-MITCH!
-MITCH!

30:46.061 --> 30:47.367
-TURN IT UPSIDE DOWN.

30:47.976 --> 30:49.804
YOU'RE GONNA LOWER IT
ON HIS HEAD

30:49.935 --> 30:50.849
WHEN THE WAVE COMES.

30:53.634 --> 30:54.722
HERE COMES THE WAVE.

30:54.853 --> 30:56.202
LOCK IT DOWN.

31:00.684 --> 31:02.077
OKAY, PULL IT OFF.

31:02.208 --> 31:03.687
DIG! DIG!

31:07.169 --> 31:08.736
-HERE COMES ANOTHER ONE.

31:22.184 --> 31:23.707
-GOT THIS ARM?
-YEAH.

31:23.838 --> 31:25.144
-CAN YOU GET
THE OTHER LEG, MITCH?

31:35.502 --> 31:36.372
-OKAY, PULL IT OFF.

31:36.503 --> 31:38.287
DIG!

31:38.418 --> 31:40.550
HERE WE GO.
I GOT A LEG.

31:40.681 --> 31:41.900
LET'S GET HIM
OUT OF HERE.

31:43.466 --> 31:44.598
-I CAN'T MOVE HIM.

31:44.728 --> 31:46.469
I CAN'T MOVE HIM, MITCH.

31:47.949 --> 31:48.732
-OKAY, ON THREE.

31:48.863 --> 31:50.517
ONE, TWO, THREE.

31:51.170 --> 31:52.606
-TURN HIM OVER.
-EASY!

31:55.914 --> 31:57.306
-THAT WAS GREAT, MITCH.

31:57.437 --> 31:58.655
THANKS FOR YOUR HELP.

31:58.786 --> 32:00.048
-WE'RE SORRY.

32:01.006 --> 32:02.137
BYE, GAYLE.

32:02.659 --> 32:03.965
-THANKS.

32:04.096 --> 32:05.532
-THANK YOU.

32:10.841 --> 32:12.713
-THE CULPRITS ARE FLEEING.

32:13.670 --> 32:15.020
-DON'T WORRY.

32:16.586 --> 32:18.284
WORRYING ABOUT WHAT VERON'S
GONNA DO TO THEM

32:18.414 --> 32:20.329
WHEN HE COMES TO
WILL BE PUNISHMENT ENOUGH.

32:22.897 --> 32:24.681
-I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT HAPPENED.

32:24.812 --> 32:26.988
-ONE MINUTE I'M KISSING YOU
AND THE NEXT MINUTE
I'VE GOT MY LIPS

32:27.119 --> 32:28.772
PRESSED AGAINST LARRY VERON'S.

32:29.599 --> 32:31.427
UGH.

32:31.558 --> 32:33.429
-WELL...

32:34.474 --> 32:36.171
SURE HAD
AN INTERESTING DAY.

32:36.302 --> 32:38.304
-IT'S BEEN A WILD ONE,
THAT'S FOR SURE.

32:40.132 --> 32:42.612
-WELL...
-YEAH.

32:43.700 --> 32:45.572
-I GUESS SOME THINGS...

32:46.225 --> 32:47.835
ARE JUST LEFT UNFINISHED.

32:48.531 --> 32:50.969
-I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE IT'S FOR THE BEST.

32:54.407 --> 32:55.625
-GUESS I'D BETTER GO CHANGE.

32:55.756 --> 32:56.713
-OKAY.

32:57.366 --> 32:58.802
-UM, DO YOU MIND
IF I USE YOUR SHOWER?

32:59.368 --> 33:01.675
-NO, NO. GO ON.
I MEAN, YOU KNOW,

33:01.805 --> 33:04.330
BELIEVE ME, I'LL BE IN THERE
RIGHT AFTER YOU ARE.

33:05.026 --> 33:06.985
-OKAY.
-OKAY.

33:12.425 --> 33:14.122
-[WATER RUNNING]

33:14.253 --> 33:18.170
-♪ I CAN HEAR THE CARS
OUT ON THE STREET ♪

33:18.953 --> 33:23.610
♪ AS I LIE AWAKE AND WATCH YOU
WHILE YOU SLEEP ♪

33:24.176 --> 33:27.918
♪ IT SEEMS THAT IT WAS
ONLY YESTERDAY ♪

33:29.137 --> 33:30.704
♪ WHEN I TOOK YOUR HAND

33:30.834 --> 33:33.576
♪ AND CARRIED YOU AWAY

33:34.099 --> 33:37.928
♪ YOU AND I WERE YOUNG AND FREE ♪

33:39.191 --> 33:43.543
♪ ALL OF THE WORLD WAS WAITING TO SEE

33:44.239 --> 33:48.635
♪ IF WE WERE JUST DREAMING, YEAH YEAH ♪

33:50.158 --> 33:52.943
♪ AHH, YEAH

33:56.686 --> 34:00.690
♪ WE NEVER HAD A SECOND CHANCE

34:02.170 --> 34:07.001
♪ WHO COULD HAVE KNOWN
THAT TIME WOULD PASS ♪

34:07.132 --> 34:10.525
♪ RIGHT THROUGH OUR HANDS

34:12.440 --> 34:16.924
♪ LOVE WAS STRONG, I REMEMBER

34:17.751 --> 34:20.754
♪ FOR SO LONG

34:20.884 --> 34:23.061
♪ WE HAD IT ALL

34:23.190 --> 34:27.413
♪ JUST COULDN'T HOLD ON

34:30.110 --> 34:33.766
♪ LOVE WAS STRONG

34:37.945 --> 34:41.295
♪ NOW THAT I FOUND YOU AGAIN

34:42.906 --> 34:47.346
♪ NOW THAT OUR HEARTS
HAD A CHANCE TO MEND ♪

34:48.042 --> 34:51.263
♪ I CAN'T WAIT ANOTHER DAY TO TELL YOU ♪

34:51.393 --> 34:57.312
♪ JUST WHAT I MEAN WHEN I SAY

34:59.009 --> 35:00.924
-OH, JOHN.

35:06.539 --> 35:07.844
-WHO'S JOHN?

35:11.761 --> 35:13.807
-HE'S A MAN
THAT I'VE BEEN SEEING.

35:14.634 --> 35:18.290
-NOW?
WITH YOUR EYES CLOSED,
YOU'RE SEEING HIM NOW?

35:19.160 --> 35:20.596
-I DON'T KNOW.

35:22.555 --> 35:24.165
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU DON'T KNOW.

35:24.818 --> 35:27.081
YOU HAVE TO KNOW
WHO YOU WERE THINKING ABOUT.

35:30.171 --> 35:31.651
-I NEVER KNOW.

35:34.436 --> 35:36.917
I'VE BEEN SEEING JOHN
FOR ABOUT A YEAR.

35:37.744 --> 35:39.572
AND HE'S ASKED ME
TO MARRY HIM.

35:41.617 --> 35:43.271
BUT SOMETIMES
WHEN I'M WITH HIM,

35:43.402 --> 35:45.186
I START THINKING
ABOUT YOU.

35:49.364 --> 35:50.452
-DO YOU CALL OUT MY NAME?

35:51.975 --> 35:53.238
-I HAVE.
YEAH.

35:57.198 --> 35:59.374
BUT HE UNDERSTOOD.

35:59.505 --> 36:01.768
IN FACT, IT WAS JOHN WHO WAS
THE ONE WHO URGED ME TO COME
TO THIS REUNION.

36:05.293 --> 36:08.166
HE SAID I SHOULD SORT OUT
MY FEELINGS ABOUT YOU,

36:08.296 --> 36:09.384
AND THAT...

36:11.256 --> 36:14.172
THAT IF I WAS IN LOVE WITH YOU,
I SHOULD EITHER GET BACK
TOGETHER WITH YOU,

36:14.302 --> 36:15.608
OR LET YOU GO.

36:25.139 --> 36:26.575
-IT'S NOT ABOUT LOVE.

36:26.706 --> 36:28.142
IS IT?

36:32.146 --> 36:33.669
I'LL ALWAYS LOVE YOU.

36:35.018 --> 36:36.194
I KNOW THAT.

36:38.021 --> 36:39.719
AND I HOPE YOU'LL
ALWAYS LOVE ME.

36:45.377 --> 36:46.769
MAYBE IT'S TIME, HUH?

36:51.252 --> 36:52.949
MAYBE IT'S TIME FOR BOTH
OF US TO LET GO.

36:53.080 --> 36:54.603
-YES.

36:58.694 --> 37:00.043
-OKAY.

37:05.962 --> 37:06.833
-YOU KNOW WHAT TONIGHT IS?

37:09.314 --> 37:10.402
-NO.
WHAT?

37:11.316 --> 37:13.056
-IT'S OUR GRADUATION.

37:14.493 --> 37:15.407
-OH.

37:28.158 --> 37:31.249
-[LAUGHING]

38:04.064 --> 38:04.934
-HOW YOU DOING?

38:05.065 --> 38:06.066
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

38:06.849 --> 38:07.981
-UH...

38:08.677 --> 38:10.113
YESTERDAY AFTERNOON,

38:10.679 --> 38:13.116
I LEFT OUR BABY GIRL
UNDER YOUR TOWER.

38:13.987 --> 38:16.511
I'M REALLY SORRY.
I MEAN, I KNOW IT WAS WRONG.

38:16.642 --> 38:18.296
IT'S JUST THAT MY WIFE...

38:18.426 --> 38:20.472
WANTED TO GIVE HER
UP FOR ADOPTION, AND I JUST...

38:22.474 --> 38:23.866
BUT THINGS ARE
OKAY NOW.

38:23.997 --> 38:25.651
SO I'M HERE
TO PICK HER UP.

38:30.264 --> 38:31.744
-SHAUNI.
-HEY.

38:32.832 --> 38:34.268
-THIS HERE IS
DAN GERSON.

38:34.399 --> 38:36.009
HE SAYS HE'S
THE BABY'S FATHER.

38:36.139 --> 38:37.532
-I AM HER FATHER.

38:37.663 --> 38:38.838
-WELL, WAIT A MINUTE.

38:38.968 --> 38:40.143
WAIT.

38:41.493 --> 38:44.539
WHEN WE FIND SOMETHING
ON THE BEACH AND SOMEBODY
COMES HERE TO CLAIM IT,

38:44.670 --> 38:46.149
WE AT LEAST MAKE THEM
DESCRIBE IT.

38:46.280 --> 38:48.891
-[CRIES]
-SO, WHAT COLOR EYES
DOES HE HAVE?

38:50.284 --> 38:51.720
-IT'S A SHE.

38:51.851 --> 38:54.201
HER NAME'S ELIZABETH
AND SHE HAS BLUE EYES.

38:54.854 --> 38:56.856
AND IF YOU'LL LOOK,
A MOLE ON HER RIGHT THIGH.

39:05.604 --> 39:06.779
OKAY?

39:10.348 --> 39:11.871
COME HERE, DARLING.
-[CRIES]

39:12.001 --> 39:12.872
-THANK YOU.

39:14.569 --> 39:15.396
OKAY.

39:16.266 --> 39:17.833
-WAIT A MINUTE, DAN.

39:17.964 --> 39:19.139
UM...

39:20.836 --> 39:22.272
JUST DO ME A FAVOR,
WOULD YOU?

39:24.231 --> 39:27.016
WRITE DOWN PART OF WHAT
YOU WROTE ON THE NOTE.

39:27.147 --> 39:28.104
-SURE.

39:29.932 --> 39:31.281
-HEY!

39:31.412 --> 39:33.327
-[BABY CRYING]
-STOP HIM!

39:33.936 --> 39:35.808
WATCH THE BABY.
WATCH THE BABY.

39:35.938 --> 39:38.680
-GOT A LADY HERE WHO SAYS
SHE'S THE MOTHER.

39:38.811 --> 39:39.942
-ELIZABETH!

39:40.073 --> 39:41.683
-[CRYING]

39:43.119 --> 39:45.426
-IT'S OKAY.
YES, IT'S OKAY.

39:45.557 --> 39:47.385
IT'S OKAY.
MAMA'S HERE.
MAMA'S HERE.

39:47.515 --> 39:50.213
-MAMA'S HERE.
-OH GOD, I NEVER SHOULD
HAVE LEFT YOU ALONE.

39:50.866 --> 39:53.042
I'LL NEVER LEAVE YOU
ALONE AGAIN. I PROMISE.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.654
AND HE'LL NEVER
TAKE YOU AWAY FROM ME.

39:55.784 --> 39:57.960
IT'S OKAY.
YEAH.

39:58.091 --> 39:59.222
OKAY.

40:00.920 --> 40:03.662
-SO, THE EX-HUSBAND
TRACKED HER DOWN HERE,

40:03.792 --> 40:05.403
TRIED TO STEAL
THE BABY.

40:05.533 --> 40:06.839
-THAT'S WHY SHE
LEFT HER WITH US

40:06.969 --> 40:08.362
UNTIL SHE COULD
GET AWAY FROM HIM.

40:09.319 --> 40:12.235
-THAT'S RIGHT, BUT,
HE CAUGHT HER, MADE HER
TELL HIM WHERE THE BABY WAS.

40:13.019 --> 40:15.717
SO, GARNER TOOK HIM DOWNTOWN
TO SORT THE WHOLE THING OUT.
THERE YOU HAVE IT.

40:17.545 --> 40:20.461
YOU KNOW, IT'S A GOOD THING
I HAVE GREAT INSTINCTS
ABOUT BABIES.

40:22.463 --> 40:23.899
HEY, HEY!

40:24.509 --> 40:26.032
-SO, MITCH,

40:26.162 --> 40:28.077
HOW WAS THE REUNION, HUH?
PRETTY BORING I BET.

40:36.738 --> 40:38.261
-IT HAD ITS MOMENTS.

40:45.660 --> 40:48.620
HEY, HOW WAS DISNEYLAND?
-GREAT!

41:24.656 --> 41:25.657
-HEY!

41:27.746 --> 41:28.703
OVER HERE.

41:41.586 --> 41:44.327
[PLAYFUL CHATTER]
